        <h2>
      <a href="/?q=node/46757">89/12</a>
    </h2>
    <span property="dc:title" content="89/12" class="rdf-meta element-hidden"></span>
  
  <div class="content clearfix">
    <div class="field field-name-field-ms-title field-type-text field-label-above"><div class="field-label">MS Title:&nbsp;</div><div class="field-items"><div class="field-item even">George Adams papers</div></div></div><div class="field field-name-field-ms-records field-type-text field-label-above"><div class="field-label">MS Date:&nbsp;</div><div class="field-items"><div class="field-item even">[1926?]</div></div></div><div class="field field-name-field-ms-extent field-type-text field-label-above"><div class="field-label">MS Extent:&nbsp;</div><div class="field-items"><div class="field-item even">1 file (3 items)</div></div></div><div class="field field-name-field-ms-physical-description field-type-text field-label-above"><div class="field-label">MS Physical description:&nbsp;</div><div class="field-items"><div class="field-item even">manuscript, typescript, photocopies, photographs</div></div></div><div class="field field-name-field-ms-historical-note field-type-text-long field-label-above"><div class="field-label">MS Historical note:&nbsp;</div><div class="field-items"><div class="field-item even"><p>George Adams and his wife Elizabeth (born Dunlop), with children, emigrated from Hertfordshire to Natal in 1850. They sailed on the 'Emily' under arrangement with W. J. Irons Christian Emigration and Colonization Society. The Adams family settled at Umhlanga where George farmed intermittently, although he also worked as a government surveyor. After the death of his first wife in 1867 he married Mary Ann Henderson a year later. George Adams died at Verulam in 1900.</p>
</div></div></div><div class="field field-name-field-ms-digitised field-type-list-text field-label-above"><div class="field-label">MS File list:&nbsp;</div><div class="field-items"><div class="field-item even">Available at KCAL</div></div></div><div class="field field-name-field-ms-bibliography field-type-text-long field-label-above"><div class="field-label">MS Bibliography:&nbsp;</div><div class="field-items"><div class="field-item even"><p>Clark, J. <em>Natal settler-agent</em>. Cape Town: Balkema, 1972</p>
<p>Spenser, S. O'B. <em>British settlers in Natal 1824-1857, vol 1.</em>Pietermaritzburg: University of Natal Press, 1981</p>
</div></div></div><div class="field field-name-field-ms-shelf field-type-text field-label-above"><div class="field-label">MS Shelf:&nbsp;</div><div class="field-items"><div class="field-item even">ADA</div></div></div><div class="field field-name-field-ms-provenance field-type-text field-label-above"><div class="field-label">MS Provenance:&nbsp;</div><div class="field-items"><div class="field-item even">Donation</div></div></div><div class="field field-name-field-ms-local-system-number field-type-text field-label-above"><div class="field-label">MS Local system number:&nbsp;</div><div class="field-items"><div class="field-item even">KCAL265177</div></div></div><div class="field field-name-taxonomy-vocabulary-6 field-type-taxonomy-term-reference field-label-above clearfix"><h3 class="field-label">Manuscript Inventory: </h3><ul class="links"><li class="taxonomy-term-reference-0"><a href="/?q=taxonomy/term/657" typeof="skos:Concept" property="rdfs:label skos:prefLabel" datatype="">Adams, George /Papers</a></li></ul></div>  </div>

